# One-path-per-line manifest of upstream files Fox does NOT ship.
# Applied via `xargs rm -f` after the upstream COPY in packages/integration/Dockerfile.
# Populated in Phase 2 (upstream onboarding tests) and Phase 7 (static/onboarding.js).
#
# Consumer convention: lines starting with `#` and blank lines MUST be
# stripped before piping to xargs. Phase 7 / Phase 8 Dockerfile commands
# use `grep -v '^\s*$\|^\s*#' .fox-removals | xargs -r rm -f --` for this.
# Do not write paths beginning with `#` and do not allow free-form prose
# inline with path entries.
